<html>
    <%- include('./partials/head.ejs') %>
    <body>

        <div class="contentView">

            <%- include('./partials/nav.ejs') %>

            <div class="mainWindow">
                <div class="contentWindow">
                    <h2>What is Campaign Coordinator?</h2>
                    <p>Campaign Coordinator is a D&D companion application. It allows dungeon masters and players to be able to see and change information about the game in a synchronized location. Campaign Coordinator is currently a work in progress. Below is a list of planned features. </p>
                    <h3>Planned Features</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strike>Chat</strike></li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Private Messages</li>
                            <li><strike>Dice Rolling</strike></li>
                        </ul>
                        <li><strike>Spectator Mode</strike></li>
                        <li>Inventory Manager</li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>DM can add & remove items</li>
                            <li>Players can view item details</li>
                        </ul>
                        <li>Character Creation</li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>5e D&D options</li>
                            <li>Custom options</li>
                        </ul>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="contentWindow">
                    <h2>How do I use Campaign Coordinator?</h2>
                    <p>To use Campaign Coordinator you should first have a basic understanding of how to play 5th Edition Dungeons and Dragons.</p>
                    <p>Each player and the Dungeon Master of your game will need to create an account. The Dungeon Master should create a game and provide the name and password for the game to each of the players. Click <a href="./games" style="color:var(--accentColor)">here</a> to go directly to the game page.  </p>
                    <p>Each player should create a character under the characters page. Click <a href="./characters" style="color:var(--accentColor)">here</a> to go directly there. </p>
                    <p>After creating a character you should navigate to the games page found <a href="./games" style="color:var(--accentColor)">here</a> and join the game with the password and name provided to you by your Dungeon Master.
                </div>

            </div>
            <%- include('./partials/footer.ejs') %>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
